reviews.review_text:
Initial thoughts on sounds recorded Beautiful opening. Plenty of excitement from the audience before the band starts playing their notes.

Vocals are center and distant.  I can't hear every note Phil is playing and it's not well defined but when he's dropping the low stuff you can hear it and feel it.

Brent sits well in the mix.  Drums are muffled and subdued.  Snare and hi-hat are sufficient enough to know where the beat is.

Initial thoughts are that all members are sufficiently present in the mix with the exception of the drums which seem to get lost in the space inside the coliseum.

Definitely listenable!  Thank you, taper.
